SIMULATION REPORT
Pipeline Processor Design using Verilog HDL
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objective

To design and simulate a simple pipelined processor capable of demonstrating instruction flow through multiple pipeline stages using Verilog HDL.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Software Used

Xilinx Vivado
Verilog HDL

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pipeline Stages Implemented

Instruction Fetch (IF)
Instruction Decode (ID)
Execute (EX)
Write Back (WB)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Instructions Used

Instruction		Operation

03			ADD
42			SUB
85			LOAD

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Simulation Procedure

The pipeline processor module was designed using Verilog HDL.
A separate testbench was created to generate the clock signal for processor operation.
Behavioral simulation was run in Xilinx Vivado.
Waveforms were observed to verify correct movement of instructions through different pipeline stages.

=========================================================================================================================================================
Waveform Analysis

The waveform shows the operation of the pipelined processor during different clock cycles. Initially, all pipeline registers contain zero values because the
processor starts in an empty state. As the clock signal toggles, instructions are fetched sequentially from the instruction memory and move through different
pipeline stages such as IF_ID, ID_EX, and EX_WB. The instruction 03 performs the ADD operation and produces the result 0F (decimal 15). 
The instruction 42 performs the SUB operation and generates the result 05 (decimal 5). The instruction 85 performs the LOAD operation and loads the
value 19 (decimal 25). The waveform also shows the program counter (pc) incrementing correctly, confirming proper instruction fetching and pipeline execution.
Overall, the waveform verifies correct instruction flow, pipeline stage shifting, arithmetic execution, and write back operations in the processor.

